1
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> How was it, Doctor?</i>

2
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:41,533
<i>We were able to revive her
and save her.</i>

3
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:46,467
<i>But we still have to
put her in the ICU.</i>

4
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:47,667
<i> Thank you.</i>

5
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:48,900
<i> Thank you, Lord.</i>

6
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>I won't let them get away
with what they did to you.</i>

7
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,600
<i> So, wake up.</i>

8
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:58,133
<i>I want you to see what
I will do to them.</i>

9
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:01,600
<i> Andeng.</i>

10
00:01:01,733 --> 00:01:04,167
<i> I missed calling you "Andeng".</i>

11
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,533
<i> I missed it, too.</i>

12
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:07,767
<i> We will rebuild our family.</i>

13
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:10,233
<i> What happened? Tell me.</i>

14
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:12,367
<i> What happened?</i>

15
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,800
<i> Wait!</i>

16
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:15,500
<i> Come on!</i>

17
00:01:18,033 --> 00:01:20,867
<i> How did this happen?</i>

18
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,967
<i>Jessica's been in an accident,
and no one told me?</i>

19
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:27,067
<i>There's one more
thing I want to ask.</i>

20
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,733
<i>I hope you can also welcome
Jessica as part of our family.</i>

21
00:01:29,867 --> 00:01:33,267
<i>If possible, I'd like her to be
the youngest of our family.</i>

22
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:36,833
<i>Even Manuel doesn't know
what happened to our daughter?</i>

23
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:38,700
<i> You people are monsters!</i>

24
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:39,900
<i> All of you!</i>

25
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:45,700
Are you and Jessica not okay?

26
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:46,733
Like Coleen?

27
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:53,800
No, Dad.

28
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,967
Then what's the matter?

29
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,100
Dad...

30
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:14,600
Something bad
happened to Jessica.

31
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,333
What happened?

32
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:22,333
Was it Hazel again?

33
00:02:22,467 --> 00:02:23,067
Manuel!

34
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,067
Manuel!

35
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,000
Wait!

36
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:25,433
Hazel!

37
00:02:28,033 --> 00:02:28,967
What did you do to
Jessica this time?

38
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:31,167
Did you hurt her again?

39
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:34,867
Manuel, I didn't do
anything to Jessica.

40
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:39,800
Coleen did.

41
00:02:42,733 --> 00:02:43,933
Coleen did something to her.

42
00:02:46,467 --> 00:02:47,333
Manuel...

43
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,000
Manuel, our daughter.

44
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,933
Coleen pushed her on the road.

45
00:02:57,367 --> 00:02:59,467
Jessica was hit by a car.

46
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:09,200
She didn't just hurt her.

47
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,633
She's the reason

48
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:14,533
why our daughter is fighting
for her life.

49
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:19,800
Our daughter is fighting
for her life, Manuel.

50
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,367
Manuel.

51
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:25,667
It's true!

52
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,167
Why don't you tell the truth?

53
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:29,067
You want her gone!

54
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:33,733
She tried to kill
our daughter, Manuel.

55
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:38,800
And they're so bad,
they didn't tell you.

56
00:03:38,933 --> 00:03:42,433
Manuel, our daughter!

57
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:45,233
Our daughter is fighting
for her life!

58
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,633
My God! Our daughter!

59
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:48,633
Manuel!

60
00:03:48,767 --> 00:03:49,667
What do we do?

61
00:03:51,567 --> 00:03:54,100
I can't bear the thought
of losing Jessica.

62
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:55,067
I can't bear it if we lose her!

63
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,333
- That's enough.
- No! No! No!

64
00:03:57,467 --> 00:03:59,167
Why are you making me leave?

65
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,533
Let's go!

66
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:02,067
Why didn't you tell Manuel?

67
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,900
-And now you're making me leave?
- Stop it.

68
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,100
No!

69
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:06,200
Let's go!

70
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,567
Manuel, I won't go anywhere!

71
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,300
Manuel, they kept it from you!

72
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:11,100
They're so horrible!

73
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:12,267
Jessica!

74
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,567
Come on!

75
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:14,367
Manuel!

76
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,300
- Let's go!
- Manuel!

77
00:04:16,433 --> 00:04:18,733
Manuel!

78
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:19,533
Dad.

79
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,833
Dad, that's not true.

80
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:27,000
I didn't try to
kill Jessica, Dad.

81
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:29,733
Dear.

82
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:31,533
What really happened?

83
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,600
Tell us.

84
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,467
Tell us, dear.

85
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:40,500
Mom.

86
00:04:40,633 --> 00:04:41,200
I'm sorry.

87
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:43,867
I can't really recall.

88
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:48,033
It happened so fast.

89
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:49,433
It happened so fast.

90
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:53,633
I was holding Jessica.

91
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:55,867
I was holding her.

92
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,033
I was holding Jessica.

93
00:04:58,167 --> 00:04:59,300
You didn't do anything wrong,
Coleen.

94
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:00,600
It wasn't your fault.

95
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:08,567
Why didn't any of you tell us
about what happened to Jessica?

96
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:13,233
We were just thinking about Dad.

97
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,767
We were worried that something
might happen to him

98
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:17,967
if he were to hear about it.

99
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,433
What about me?

100
00:05:19,567 --> 00:05:22,000
You should've told me!

101
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:25,633
So I would know how to
face Hazel's wrath.

102
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:35,067
If I only knew that
Jessica was in danger,

103
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:38,500
I would've comforted Hazel.

104
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:40,067
I'm a mother, too.

105
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:44,533
So I know how
she feels right now!

106
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,300
I understand her anger.

107
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:52,900
Sorry, Mom.

108
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:54,800
We were just waiting for
the right time to tell you.

109
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:57,867
I'll go and see Jessica.

110
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,700
Dad.

111
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,233
Dad.

112
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:01,567
Felma, please come with.

113
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:02,800
I'll go and see Jessica.

114
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:04,633
Dad, wait. Don't force yourself.

115
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:06,833
Jessica needs me now.

116
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:09,000
I know, Dad. But don't move yet.

117
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:10,100
Your sister needs me.

118
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:13,067
Manuel, calm down.

119
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,733
- Felma, come with me.
- Calm down.

120
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:17,600
Come with me, please.

121
00:06:17,733 --> 00:06:18,667
Jessica needs me.

122
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,200
- She needs me.
- Yes, I'll go with you.

123
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,600
I'll go with you.

124
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:24,300
We'll go and see Jessica.

125
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:29,567
But let's talk to
Dr. Richard first.

126
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:32,767
Calm down.

127
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,400
Jessica needs me right now.

128
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:36,000
My daughter needs me.

129
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:37,667
Dad, please listen to Mom.

130
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:41,033
Please, come with me.

131
00:06:52,467 --> 00:06:55,833
Friend, get some rest for now.

132
00:06:55,967 --> 00:06:57,500
Try to get even a nap.

133
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:03,600
Alice...

134
00:07:08,067 --> 00:07:11,033
These 24 hours
feel like forever.

135
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:17,300
I wish...

136
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,700
it were easier.

137
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,167
I wish it were faster.

138
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:36,000
If only it took one, two,
or three hours,

139
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:44,500
and we'd already know if the
patient's out of danger.

140
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:47,800
If...

141
00:07:51,867 --> 00:07:55,367
If she's survived the time
death was supposed to take her.

142
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,967
Come on. Don't say that.

143
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,133
Jessica is a fighter.

144
00:08:00,267 --> 00:08:02,500
She'll get through this.

145
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:03,433
Don't be impatient.

146
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:05,600
My goddaughter will wake up.

147
00:08:13,933 --> 00:08:14,800
Hazel...

148
00:08:20,367 --> 00:08:22,300
may I see our daughter?

149
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,233
Jessica, dear.

150
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:48,033
Do you hear me?

151
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,767
<i> I wish I had just died.</i>

152
00:08:54,933 --> 00:08:56,567
<i> Dad, don't say that.</i>

153
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:59,933
<i>I can't bear it
if I lose you, Dad.</i>

154
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:01,767
<i> I can't bear it.</i>

155
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:04,200
<i> I'll be a burden to you.</i>

156
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:07,367
<i> Dad, don't think that way.</i>

157
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,700
<i>You'll never be a burden to me.</i>

158
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,167
<i>And I really don't mind
taking care of you, Dad.</i>

159
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,333
<i>Remember, ever since
I was a baby,</i>

160
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:16,167
<i> you took good care of me.</i>

161
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:21,833
<i>Do you plan to tell your
original family</i>

162
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,533
<i> about your situation?</i>

163
00:09:23,667 --> 00:09:25,733
<i>They don't care about me
anymore.</i>

164
00:09:25,867 --> 00:09:27,467
<i> That's not true.</i>

165
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,233
<i>I'm sure Miss Felma
cares about you.</i>

166
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,800
<i> Hi, Dad.</i>

167
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:35,733
<i> How are you?</i>

168
00:09:43,233 --> 00:09:44,833
<i>I'll just stay
in a nursing home.</i>

169
00:09:44,967 --> 00:09:47,667
<i> Dad, I don't want that.</i>

170
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:51,233
<i> I won't let you do that, Dad.</i>

171
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:54,867
<i>I'll do everything to bring you
back to the Philippines.</i>

172
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,767
<i>Dad, I made a promise
last time, remember?</i>

173
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,333
<i> You're finally going home.</i>

174
00:09:59,467 --> 00:10:01,000
<i> Let's go.</i>

175
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:02,700
<i> Dad, she's here.</i>

176
00:10:11,167 --> 00:10:14,233
Dear, I know you're strong.

177
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:17,700
I know you can get through this.

178
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,567
Just like before.

179
00:10:25,367 --> 00:10:25,967
Dear...

180
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,133
please keep fighting.

181
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:30,867
Don't give up.

182
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:37,400
Because I haven't
made it up to you yet.

183
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:44,467
You're always the one
taking care of me.

184
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:49,600
Dear, it's my turn
to take care of you.

185
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:52,433
It's my turn.

186
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,800
Please wake up, dear.

187
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,000
Wake up, okay?

188
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,300
And I'll take care of you.

189
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:14,433
Mom, you shouldn't have
left Dad with Hazel.

190
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:17,233
What was the point of
bringing him home

191
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:18,700
if you were just going
to send him back?

192
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:27,167
Son, do you really think
she'd take your dad away?

193
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:29,900
She'll leave Jessica?

194
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:30,767
I don't know, Mom.

195
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,233
I don't know how
the devil thinks.

196
00:11:32,367 --> 00:11:33,200
She's a devil.

197
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,933
I understand your fear.

198
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:44,533
But, son,
Hazel won't leave Jessica.

199
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:47,300
Not now.

200
00:11:47,433 --> 00:11:52,400
Mom, she's hurting
her own child.

201
00:11:52,533 --> 00:11:55,033
My brother's right, Mom.

202
00:11:55,167 --> 00:11:59,933
She can abandon our
sister for our dad.

203
00:12:00,067 --> 00:12:01,467
She's desperate.

204
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:07,833
Don't think that way.

205
00:12:10,633 --> 00:12:16,100
Even the worst mother
in the world...

206
00:12:18,267 --> 00:12:23,433
would never abandon her child
when their life is on the line.

207
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:29,500
Instead of thinking all
sorts of things,

208
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:35,300
just join me, let's pray for
Jessica.

209
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,567
Andeng, sit down.

210
00:12:48,633 --> 00:12:50,033
Let's pray.

211
00:12:56,633 --> 00:13:01,867
Hazel, thank you for
letting me see Jessica.

212
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,167
Jessica, dear.

213
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,933
Your dad and I are here.

214
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:20,733
We're fighting with you.

215
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,567
Don't give up, okay?

216
00:13:25,133 --> 00:13:26,200
I'm just here, dear.

217
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,667
You're not alone.

218
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,633
Your fight is our fight.

219
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:40,033
Manuel.

220
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:41,767
Did you see that?

221
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:42,867
Did you see that?

222
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:47,767
Dear.

223
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:53,233
That's it, dear. Fight.

224
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:56,867
Just keep on fighting.

225
00:13:57,867 --> 00:13:59,867
Remember that I love you.

226
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:02,767
I love you so much.

227
00:14:03,867 --> 00:14:05,233
We're here.

228
00:14:06,467 --> 00:14:08,200
Dear, we're waiting for you.

229
00:14:09,267 --> 00:14:10,867
We'll wait for you, Jessica.

230
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:16,933
- Keep on figthing.
- Jessica.

231
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,133
Jessica!

232
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:26,933
- Jessica!
- No!

233
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:27,867
No!

234
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,900
No! No!

235
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:33,000
- Jessica, don't leave me!
- Nurse! Nurse!

236
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:34,667
Code blue! Code blue!

237
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,367
Code blue! Please call...

238
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,400
My child! Dear!

239
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:39,667
Jessica!

240
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:40,867
Dear, hold on!

241
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,200
Hold on, please wait!

242
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,200
Doc!

243
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:44,200
Doc!

244
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:45,400
Code blue!

245
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:46,300
Jessica!

246
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:47,467
Code blue!

247
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:52,600
Hang in there, dear!

248
00:14:52,733 --> 00:14:55,133
Hang in there!

249
00:14:55,267 --> 00:14:56,367
Hang in there, dear!

250
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,433
Start CPR. Prep epinephrine.

251
00:14:58,567 --> 00:14:59,467
Bag her now.

252
00:15:00,867 --> 00:15:03,400
- Jessice, keep fighting.
- Epi, 1mg IV. Push!

253
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:05,633
Please don't take her!

254
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:06,933
No!

255
00:15:07,067 --> 00:15:08,467
Another round.

256
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:11,033
- Continue CPR.
- Dear, keep fighting.

257
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:13,167
- Another dose of epinephrine.
- Jessica!

258
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,967
Dear, fight for me.

259
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:16,167
1mg, amp.

260
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:21,133
Dear, don't give up.

261
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:22,633
Please don't.

262
00:15:22,767 --> 00:15:24,267
Stop compressions.

263
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,667
Prepare defib.

264
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:33,867
Prep defib. Charge to 160.

265
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:38,000
- Clear!
- Jessica.

266
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:40,100
Jessica!

267
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:42,267
Continue CPR.

268
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,000
Jessica, dear!

269
00:15:45,567 --> 00:15:46,967
Dear!

270
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,100
Charge to 200.

271
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:51,267
Clear.

272
