286
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:19,867
No!

287
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,000
No!

288
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,200
No!

289
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:23,767
Jessica!

290
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,133
Why did you stop!

291
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:26,133
No!

292
00:16:26,267 --> 00:16:27,133
Wait!

293
00:16:27,267 --> 00:16:30,267
Jessica! My child!

294
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:33,700
Jessica!

295
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,233
Why did you stop?

296
00:16:36,367 --> 00:16:37,900
Jessica isn't dead yet!

297
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:38,733
She isn't dead yet!

298
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:39,833
Wait!

299
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:41,100
Jessica, dear!

300
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:46,033
- Jessica!
- No! No! No!

301
00:16:46,167 --> 00:16:48,700
Jessica!

302
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:49,700
No!

303
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:51,500
- She isn't dead yet!
- Don't leave us!

304
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:52,567
No!

305
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:54,067
Why did you stop?

306
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,200
Jessica!

307
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,700
Jessica!

308
00:16:56,833 --> 00:17:01,267
Jessica! Jessica! Dear!

309
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,067
- Jessica!
- Jessica!

310
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,000
My daughter!

311
00:17:04,133 --> 00:17:05,067
Please wake up!

312
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:05,800
Wake up!

313
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,300
Let go of me!

314
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:10,000
Jessica!

315
00:17:10,133 --> 00:17:12,900
My daughter!

316
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:13,767
Jessica!

317
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,533
I'm telling you, darling.

318
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,767
You're just going
to get embarrassed.

319
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:19,600
Hazel won't let you
get near Jessica.

320
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:20,467
I'll beg her.

321
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,900
I want to see my goddaughter.

322
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:25,733
Manuel?

323
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:27,967
Jessica, my dear!

324
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:28,733
Bro!

325
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:32,267
My daughter!

326
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,233
Jessica!

327
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:37,133
Don't leave me, dear!

328
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:38,800
Manuel!

329
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,200
My baby!

330
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:41,100
Sweetie!

331
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:44,967
Sweetie!

332
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:01,000
<i> Lord, please save Jessica.</i>

333
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,167
<i> Please save our sister.</i>

334
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:16,067
<i>I still want to get
to know her better.</i>

335
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,033
<i>I still want to hear
her stories about Dad.</i>

336
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,800
<i>I want her to feel what it's
like to have a sister like me.</i>

337
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:39,067
Paz.

338
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:45,167
Jessica's gone.

339
00:18:52,567 --> 00:18:53,533
My God.

340
00:18:55,867 --> 00:18:56,633
Why?

341
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,200
No.

342
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,933
No.

343
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:03,633
Jessica's still young.

344
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:08,367
Jessica is still young.

345
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,767
She's still so young.

346
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:13,367
What happened?

347
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,800
No.

348
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:21,200
No.

349
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:22,900
What's going on?

350
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:31,267
Is it about Jessica?

351
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:37,533
Sweetie...

352
00:19:40,967 --> 00:19:45,833
Jessica didn't make it.

353
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,333
No.

354
00:19:51,467 --> 00:19:54,833
She can't be dead!

355
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:57,067
We haven't made up yet!

356
00:19:57,200 --> 00:20:00,000
She hasn't forgiven me!

357
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:02,667
Coleen.

358
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,400
No!

359
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:05,133
Jessica!

360
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:07,333
Wait!

361
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:08,333
Mom, I got her.

362
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:09,833
Coleen!

363
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:11,200
Dear!

364
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:33,100
Is Jessica really gone?

365
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:36,000
Let go of me!

366
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:37,833
Please, take me back to her!

367
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:39,467
Take me to Jessica!

368
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:40,100
Give it to him now.

369
00:20:40,267 --> 00:20:42,167
My daughter needs me!

370
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,567
Let go of me!

371
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:44,400
Manuel, don't! Don't!

372
00:20:44,533 --> 00:20:46,500
- Let go of me!
- Manuel, don't.

373
00:20:46,633 --> 00:20:48,300
- Let go of me!
- Manuel, don't.

374
00:20:48,433 --> 00:20:50,267
Good, good, good.

375
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:51,300
Hold him.

376
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:52,033
Okay.

377
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:53,600
Good. It's okay, it's okay.

378
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:55,367
It's okay. It's okay.

379
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:56,867
It's okay.

380
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:57,767
All right.

381
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:59,633
Nurse, VS Q2, okay?

382
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:01,367
Close bedside monitoring.

383
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:02,933
He might go hypotensive.

384
00:21:03,067 --> 00:21:04,100
Yes, Doc. I'll take care of it.

385
00:21:04,233 --> 00:21:05,133
Okay.

386
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:07,467
Miss Felma, the medication's
already here.

387
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,667
We had to sedate him
for a while.

388
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,833
You saw what happened.

389
00:21:10,967 --> 00:21:12,433
But he's safe, all right?

390
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:14,233
He's under close monitoring.

391
00:21:14,367 --> 00:21:15,600
- Okay?
- Thank you, Doctor.

392
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:16,800
Thank you, Doc.

393
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:18,200
Please assist Manuel.

394
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:28,467
Paz, I don't know
what to do anymore.

395
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,767
I don't know.

396
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:34,000
I don't even know
who to help first.

397
00:21:34,133 --> 00:21:36,367
Go to the kids first.

398
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,333
Go check on Coleen.

399
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:39,700
I'll stay here.

400
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:42,900
I'll watch over
Manuel for now, okay?

401
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:46,400
If he wakes up,
call me right away.

402
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:47,833
Thank you.

403
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,033
- Let me go!
- Coleen, wait!

404
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:04,167
- Let me go!
- Sweetheart!

405
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:05,600
I want to see Jessica!

406
00:22:05,733 --> 00:22:06,667
We want to see her, too.

407
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:09,733
But you know that
Hazel won't allow it.

408
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:12,367
Especially since she accuses you
of pushing Jessica.

409
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,400
Even if it isn't true.

410
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:16,400
Coleen has already remembered
what happened, Mom.

411
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:19,967
Mom.

412
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:24,867
Mom, I didn't push Jessica.

413
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:29,200
I pulled her because I
was apologizing to her.

414
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:32,667
But she didn't believe me, Mom.

415
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:36,033
She kept struggling.

416
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:38,767
<i>- I'm done with you all!
- Jessica, no!</i>

417
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:39,967
<i> Jessica, please.</i>

418
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:41,467
<i> I've realized my mistakes.</i>

419
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,633
<i> I'm sorry. Let's talk...</i>

420
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:44,333
<i> Let's talk about it, Jessica!</i>

421
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:46,067
<i>- Jessica!
- Let me go!</i>

422
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:49,833
<i> Jessica!</i>

423
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:53,500
I couldn't hold on to Jessica.

424
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:58,000
Mom, I promise.

425
00:22:58,133 --> 00:23:00,667
I wouldn't do that to her, Mom.

426
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,100
No.

427
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:02,900
Dear.

428
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,200
I believe you.

429
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:11,700
We believe you, sweetheart.

430
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:12,933
Okay?

431
00:23:13,067 --> 00:23:14,567
I believe you.

432
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:22,933
Jeff and I...

433
00:23:25,033 --> 00:23:26,900
consulted Attorney Yeban, Mom.

434
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:30,833
We already know
what Hazel's like.

435
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:36,533
Just in case she files
a case against Coleen.

436
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,367
What did he say?

437
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:41,300
He said we shouldn't be afraid.

438
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:45,533
We just have to prove
that Coleen didn't push Jessica.

439
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:48,500
But he warned us.

440
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:51,733
The problem might come

441
00:23:51,867 --> 00:23:57,500
if Hazel insists that Coleen
acted with malice or intent.

442
00:23:57,667 --> 00:24:01,567
She can use the fight
between Jessica and Coleen.

443
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:06,033
The time when she stormed
at FMP because Jessica got hurt.

444
00:24:06,167 --> 00:24:07,367
She can blow it up
into a major story

445
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:09,200
to make it look like Coleen
had a motive.

446
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,200
Mom...

447
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:15,533
Mom, what if Hazel
sends me to jail?

448
00:24:15,667 --> 00:24:18,233
What if she locks me up?

449
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:19,733
Mom...

450
00:24:19,867 --> 00:24:23,367
Dear, I won't let that happen.

451
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,200
Don't be afraid.

452
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:29,433
We'll fight her.

453
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,567
Okay?

454
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,600
We'll fight her together.

455
00:24:32,733 --> 00:24:33,800
That's enough, dear.

456
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:35,733
Please. Enough crying.

457
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:37,333
Stop crying.

458
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,300
Stop crying.

459
00:24:41,367 --> 00:24:42,600
Stop crying.

460
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:53,433
I'll find evidence against her.

461
00:24:53,567 --> 00:24:56,800
You won't find any evidence
because Coleen is innocent!

462
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:59,700
Won't you stop defending
your criminal daughter?

463
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:02,267
Don't you dare call
her that again.

464
00:25:02,433 --> 00:25:03,667
She's nothing like you!

465
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,600
That's a serious accusation.

466
00:25:05,733 --> 00:25:10,100
I just have to remind you,
words aren't enough.

467
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:11,267
We can't just throw
around accusations.

468
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,133
We need solid evidence.

469
00:25:13,267 --> 00:25:17,100
To be honest, you know your
condition is very delicate.

470
00:25:17,233 --> 00:25:19,333
You need to stay completely
stress-free, okay?

471
00:25:19,467 --> 00:25:20,200
Don't worry, Doctor.

472
00:25:20,333 --> 00:25:21,633
It won't happen again.

473
00:25:21,767 --> 00:25:22,767
It's just that she forbade me

474
00:25:22,900 --> 00:25:25,067
from seeing
our daughter's funeral.

475
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,600
You have the right
to see Jessica

476
00:25:28,733 --> 00:25:30,567
because you are his father.

477
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,867
Hazel will just lose control
if she sees me there.

478
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,267
She returned, Hazel.

479
00:25:35,833 --> 00:25:36,700
It's Felma.
